						               													<description>In an alternate 1985, Soviet tanks rolled across the West German border&amp;hellip;but that wasn&amp;rsquo;t the only battleground the Superpowers came to blows. &amp;#10;One of these battlegrounds was Scandinavia. This scenario pack is Volume 1 of a new series meant to address the question &amp;ldquo;What is occurring in these &amp;ldquo;Other Fires&amp;rdquo; of the Third World War.&amp;#10;The scenarios cover tank battles, small commando raids meant to shape the fate of nations, and everything in between!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents of Volume 1:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     12 scenarios for a variety of rules systems (tested with Ambush Alley and Arc of Fire, but playable with any rules set) &amp;#10;     Meticulously researched Squad and Platoon-level tables of organization and equipment for Norway, Sweden, and Finland, as well as the British Royal Marine Commandos and Soviet VDV, with input from the veterans themselves! &amp;#10;     Suggestions for special rules meant to reflect the conditions of the far north.   &amp;#10;     Notes for where to find miniatures suitable for games with these scenarios!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Come explore some of the other fighting that might have broken out in a Third World War, and see what might have happened if the Red Star advanced south under the White Lights!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
